As an introverted creative individual who is self-employed and highly privacy-conscious, running a business shouldn't feel this awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to engage with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here, you need to advertise, follow the algorithm, share your personal charm, get verified on that platform, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Videos, videos, and more videos.
1/3
This year is a year of transformation for me.
I no longer want to dedicate my money, data, and energy to large tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only push a single extroverted solution onto everyone. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by doing things a certain way.
Wish me luck!
The first step has been taken.
I left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and canceled my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and it felt great.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business over in the coming weeks.
I transferred my MX records to Proton, and now I have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
